HEADWORD: Inwreathe
<hw>In*wreathe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To surround or
encompass as with a wreath.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>enwreathe</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Resplendent locks, <qex>inwreathed</qex> with beams.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inwrought</ent>⟦br⟧
